<br>
I figured I would post another response here since I asked this question somewhere else.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://contest.thinkquest.gr.jp/tqj1999/20190/jpn/index.html">contest.thinkquest.gr.jp/...index.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
This is a really nice site even though it's completely in japanese.  It has reading practice rated from 1 star - 5 stars  (5 is the most difficult).  The nice thing about them is that there are hyperlinks on many of the words and translations on the side.  It even keeps track of the words you click on so you can check later.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.asagaku.com">www.asagaku.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
this is some sort of children's newspaper.  It's easier to read than the regular newspapers, so it's a good place to start I guess.  <br>
